{"content":"Decision: Used `asyncio.Semaphore(max_concurrent)` for concurrency control in `run_tasks` (run.py).

The implementation wraps each task in a `_run_one` coroutine that uses `async with sem:` to acquire/release the semaphore. This ensures at most `max_concurrent` tasks run simultaneously.

Why: The semaphore provides atomic acquire-on-entry/release-on-exit semantics and automatically removes cancelled waiters from its internal queue when CancelledError propagates through the `async with` context manager. This is simpler and more correct than manual tracking with counters or sets. The semaphore is the standard asyncio primitive for bounded concurrency.","wing":"workspace","room":"general","importance":3,"source":"run.py"}

